16/04/2009
SERBIA, Belgrade -- The country formally files its appeal against Kosovo's unilateral declaration of independence before the International Court of Justice (ICJ) on Friday (April 17th), Beta agency reported on Wednesday, citing government sources. Kosovo submits its own motion as well. Next, both sides are to provide arguments in support of their positions. There is no deadline for the ICJ judges to issue their ruling, which is advisory in nature, not binding. (RTS, Beta - 15/04/09)
